MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 364c2b772391e46dba637935c558b9b2, type: 3}
  m_Name: Lion
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::MythSO
  pageNumber: 89
  mythName: Lion
  omens:
  - '1. On the brink of a disused clay pit, a potter

    shapes a bowl, telling
    a story to the dozen

    children gathered to watch. She tells of

    the Lion,
    the king of beasts. No Knight

    could slay him, but a potter was his great

    enemy.
    She avoids giving any details.'
  - '2. Horse breeders leading a dozen chargers

    toward the Seat of Power. They''re

    struggling
    to get the horses moving, as

    they''re all bowing toward the Lion''s Hex.'
  - '3. An isolated, babbling pond. A pike pokes

    its head from the water to
    cackle at

    passers-by. It can''t really speak, but

    mimics words it has
    heard. It shouts "He''s

    here for his crown" among the gibberish.'
  - '4. All steeds throw riders to the ground

    before charging off toward the
    Seat of

    Power to await the Lion''s arrival.'
  - '5. The Lion, heading toward the Seat of

    Power to peacefully take the Domain.'
  - '6. Tired herald spreads word that the Lion

    has taken the Seat of Power.
    Some

    humans remain in court, but mostly

    they''re replaced with unsuitable
    beasts.'
  verse: 'With creak and grind of time-worn wheel

    A king of all is brought to
    kneel'
  castEntries:
  - name: The Lion, Belliore, King of All Beasts
    statBlock: 'VIG 18, CLA 12, SPI 15, 10 GD

      A2 (thick hide, shaggy mane)'
    notes: 'Claws and jaws (2d8 +d10 against humans)

      Roar (all who refuse
      to bow lose d6 SPI)

      All beasts bow to him, but he loathes them.

      Hates
      the sound of wheels, terrified by fire,

      cockerels, and any beast that
      stings. Even a

      drop of weak venom is lethal to the Lion.

      Can
      speak, but resents needing to do so.'
  - name: Storytelling Potter, Niefib
    statBlock: 'VIG 10, CLA 14, SPI 18, 2 GD

      A1 (layers and layers of coats
      and cloaks)'
    notes: 'Always followed by a throng of

      infuriating children.'
  flavorTable:
    title: INFURIATING CHILDREN
    columns:
    - header: Wants
      values:
      - Entertaining
      - A very specific food
      - What you have
      - To go home
      - Something another
      - child has They don't even know
    - header: Will Not
      values:
      - Stay still
      - Use words
      - Stop crying
      - Compromise even a bit
      - Explain themselves
      - properly Stop grabbing you
  visibleByDefault: 0
  visibleMarkerPrefab: {fileID: 0}
